1
00:00:01,233 --> 00:00:02,433
<i>previously on
ghost whisperer...</i>

2
00:00:02,501 --> 00:00:03,901
I feel like i've waited
my whole life

3
00:00:03,969 --> 00:00:09,106
Just to meet you.

4
00:00:09,174 --> 00:00:11,976
Is this what our lives
have become?
one giant party?

5
00:00:12,043 --> 00:00:13,310
Both: yes!
[laughter]

6
00:00:13,378 --> 00:00:15,246
Ooh, dad's gonna get us!
he's gonna get us!

7
00:00:15,313 --> 00:00:16,981
Eli: but you feel it,
too, right?

8
00:00:17,048 --> 00:00:18,382
Every time i treat
a patient here,

9
00:00:18,450 --> 00:00:19,583
As soon as i walk
in the building...

10
00:00:19,651 --> 00:00:20,918
Lost souls,
you know?

11
00:00:20,986 --> 00:00:22,286
But it's a hospital.

12
00:00:22,354 --> 00:00:23,454
People die here.

13
00:00:23,522 --> 00:00:25,122
No, i worked
in a lot of hospitals.

14
00:00:25,190 --> 00:00:27,291
There's something different
about this one.

15
00:00:27,359 --> 00:00:29,293
[electricity flickering]

16
00:00:32,330 --> 00:00:33,397
Melinda...

17
00:00:33,465 --> 00:00:34,798
Melinda: where are they?

18
00:00:34,866 --> 00:00:36,367
Are they in danger?
aiden isn't,

19
00:00:36,434 --> 00:00:37,501
If he stays where he is.

20
00:00:37,569 --> 00:00:39,503
Aiden...

21
00:00:39,571 --> 00:00:42,439
Just stay where you are.

22
00:00:42,507 --> 00:00:44,808
Come here!
you're not safe there.

23
00:00:44,876 --> 00:00:46,410
How do you know?
i just know.

24
00:00:49,514 --> 00:00:50,648
Are you ok?
yeah.

25
00:00:50,715 --> 00:00:52,850
I made tyler stay with me,
like i was supposed to.

26
00:00:52,918 --> 00:00:54,218
Who told you that
you were supposed to?

27
00:00:54,286 --> 00:00:55,719
I don't know.
the visions i've had,

28
00:00:55,787 --> 00:00:58,389
They've been from aiden?
is he a sensitive?

29
00:00:58,456 --> 00:01:01,392
The word you're looking for
is "empath."

30
00:01:01,459 --> 00:01:03,861
He can share
other people's feelings.

31
00:01:03,929 --> 00:01:05,996
You don't
want him to know
he's connected to you?

32
00:01:06,064 --> 00:01:08,299
No. if he did,
then he'd know
that his dreams

33
00:01:08,366 --> 00:01:09,500
Aren't really his.

34
00:01:09,568 --> 00:01:11,335
I want his dreams
to belong to him

35
00:01:11,403 --> 00:01:13,103
Like any little boy.

36
00:01:13,171 --> 00:01:15,172
[crickets chirping]

37
00:01:16,174 --> 00:01:17,608
Melinda: ok.

38
00:01:17,676 --> 00:01:20,544
Time for you
to get comfy
all on your own.

39
00:01:20,612 --> 00:01:22,279
Tomorrow, we're
gonna get up early

40
00:01:22,347 --> 00:01:25,416
And we're going
to have your
favorite breakfast.

41
00:01:25,483 --> 00:01:27,585
But for right now,

42
00:01:27,652 --> 00:01:30,221
Here's
your monkey, ok?

43
00:01:30,288 --> 00:01:33,624
Good night, baby.
sweet dreams.

44
00:01:33,692 --> 00:01:35,292
Here, put your arms
in there.

45
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:36,894
There you go.

46
00:01:36,962 --> 00:01:39,096
But i don't want
to go to sleep yet.

47
00:01:39,164 --> 00:01:40,631
I'm not tired.

48
00:01:40,699 --> 00:01:43,133
Well, you're just
gonna have to give it
your best shot, ok?

49
00:01:43,201 --> 00:01:46,470
But i--i'm thirsty.

50
00:01:46,538 --> 00:01:48,205
Uh-uh, don't try to
pull that with me.

51
00:01:48,273 --> 00:01:50,107
Good night.

52
00:01:50,175 --> 00:01:51,842
I'll get the light.

53
00:01:55,547 --> 00:01:57,781
It's not even 8:00.
do you really think
he's gonna go down?

54
00:01:57,849 --> 00:02:00,384
Unheard of, right?

55
00:02:00,452 --> 00:02:02,453
[groans]

56
00:02:09,661 --> 00:02:11,895
Jim: wow.

57
00:02:11,963 --> 00:02:13,230
He's an angel.

58
00:02:13,298 --> 00:02:15,232
Hard to imagine
he's the same little guy

59
00:02:15,300 --> 00:02:17,801
Who just smeared
peanut butter
on my laptop.

60
00:02:19,204 --> 00:02:21,338
Wait a minute,
wait a minute.

61
00:02:21,406 --> 00:02:23,207
You know what this
means, don't you?

62
00:02:23,275 --> 00:02:24,742
We get a gold star?

63
00:02:24,809 --> 00:02:28,912
No, we might
actually have some
time...to ourselves.

64
00:02:28,980 --> 00:02:31,181
Uh, if i didn't have
peanut butter on my laptop.

65
00:02:31,249 --> 00:02:32,950
No, laptop's
peanut butter-free.

66
00:02:33,018 --> 00:02:34,652
I had a minute when
you were brushing
aiden's teeth.

67
00:02:34,719 --> 00:02:36,220
Wait a minute,
if we just get
the dishes done--

68
00:02:36,288 --> 00:02:38,122
Done! i did them while
you were reading to aiden.

69
00:02:38,189 --> 00:02:39,523
Well, if we can get
the laundry folded--

70
00:02:39,591 --> 00:02:41,225
Also done. clean scrubs,
in your drawer.

71
00:02:41,293 --> 00:02:42,293
I took out the trash.

72
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,927
I made aiden's lunch
for tomorrow.

73
00:02:43,995 --> 00:02:45,462
You did?
yeah.

74
00:02:45,530 --> 00:02:47,131
Ah, that is such a turn-on.

75
00:02:47,198 --> 00:02:48,932
If you did not have
to go to work tonight...

76
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,434
I don't.

77
00:02:50,502 --> 00:02:52,803
I got that
intern scott
to cover my shift.

78
00:02:54,205 --> 00:02:56,674
We have a totally free night?

79
00:02:56,741 --> 00:02:59,576
Absolutely.

80
00:02:59,644 --> 00:03:01,779
Oh!

81
00:03:01,846 --> 00:03:03,647
Come here.

82
00:03:07,886 --> 00:03:08,919
Oh!

83
00:03:21,766 --> 00:03:23,734
So, where's
your roommate?

84
00:03:23,802 --> 00:03:26,236
Uh, cramming
for a psych midterm.

85
00:03:26,304 --> 00:03:28,439
Won't be back for a while.

86
00:03:28,506 --> 00:03:29,940
[both moaning]

87
00:03:30,008 --> 00:03:31,709
Lucky us.

88
00:03:37,549 --> 00:03:39,950
You know, just in case...

89
00:03:43,321 --> 00:03:47,458
Don't move a muscle.

90
00:03:47,525 --> 00:03:48,692
Oh.

91
00:03:48,760 --> 00:03:50,627
Don't move a muscle.

92
00:03:55,367 --> 00:03:57,334
[screaming]

93
00:03:57,402 --> 00:03:59,770
[gasping]

94
00:03:59,838 --> 00:04:00,938
Oh, no!

95
00:04:01,005 --> 00:04:01,939
What kind of--what?!

96
00:04:02,006 --> 00:04:04,041
[gasping]

97
00:04:07,645 --> 00:04:09,980
What kind of person
would do this?

98
00:04:10,048 --> 00:04:11,448
I don't know!

99
00:04:11,516 --> 00:04:13,517
[cracking]

100
00:04:15,253 --> 00:04:17,788
What's happening?

101
00:04:17,856 --> 00:04:19,823
[gasping]

102
00:04:25,663 --> 00:04:27,931
Oh, no!

103
00:04:27,999 --> 00:04:30,000
[gasping]

104
00:04:31,736 --> 00:04:34,571
Maybe it wasn't
a person at all.

105
00:04:49,721 --> 00:04:51,722
[indistinct whispering]

106
00:04:57,128 --> 00:04:59,029
[gasps]

107
00:04:59,097 --> 00:05:00,464
It must be done.

108
00:05:00,532 --> 00:05:02,733
Who are you?

109
00:05:02,801 --> 00:05:05,102
Stop it before it spreads.

110
00:05:05,170 --> 00:05:06,603
Stop what?

111
00:05:06,671 --> 00:05:09,840
If it's not
too late already.

112
00:05:14,712 --> 00:05:15,979
Shush, now.

113
00:05:16,047 --> 00:05:17,948
Shush, girl.

114
00:05:19,083 --> 00:05:20,543
Your screams
won't help you.

115
00:05:20,544 --> 00:05:22,544
Whose screams?
Who are you talking to?

116
00:05:22,954 --> 00:05:25,622
[gasping]
this will hurt,

117
00:05:25,690 --> 00:05:27,257
But it'll be over
quickly.

118
00:05:29,258 --> 00:05:30,258
What are you doing?

119
00:05:33,259 --> 00:05:34,259
***

120
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:38,235
Hold still now.
melinda: no!

121
00:05:39,270 --> 00:05:41,271
[screaming]

122
00:05:44,942 --> 00:05:47,210
Child, whispering:
can you see us?

123
00:06:04,862 --> 00:06:07,864
Sync by honeybunny
www.addic7ed.com

124
00:06:19,058 --> 00:06:21,860
Jim: so with the robes
and the hushed voices,

125
00:06:21,928 --> 00:06:23,929
I mean, is there any chance
they could have been doctors

126
00:06:23,996 --> 00:06:25,764
Performing, i don't know,
some kind of operation?

127
00:06:25,832 --> 00:06:27,532
With a huge, rusty needle?

128
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,201
Well, you said it looked
like they came from
another era.

129
00:06:29,268 --> 00:06:31,036
Maybe it was the era
before sterilization.

130
00:06:31,104 --> 00:06:32,370
Yeah, or no anesthesia.

131
00:06:32,438 --> 00:06:34,005
They just kept saying,
"hold still,"

132
00:06:34,073 --> 00:06:36,241
But i could still
feel everything.

133
00:06:36,309 --> 00:06:38,743
And they couldn't see
or hear you at all.

134
00:06:38,811 --> 00:06:40,378
You know, it sounds
like one of your visions

135
00:06:40,446 --> 00:06:41,713
You've been channeling
from aiden.

136
00:06:41,781 --> 00:06:43,815
Yeah, he was awake
when i went in
to check on him.

137
00:06:43,883 --> 00:06:45,984
Hey, there weren't
any little needles

138
00:06:46,052 --> 00:06:47,819
In any of his
dreams?

139
00:06:47,887 --> 00:06:49,988
No, he doesn't remember
his ghost dreams.

140
00:06:50,056 --> 00:06:53,458
Thank god. you know,
he certainly remembers
his other dreams.

141
00:06:53,526 --> 00:06:55,293
You know, a couple
nights ago he was dreaming

142
00:06:55,361 --> 00:06:57,629
That he was flying over
a mountain made of ice cream.

143
00:06:57,697 --> 00:06:59,531
Now he wants to
learn how to skate--
mommy?

144
00:06:59,599 --> 00:07:01,867
Dad!
aha! whoo!

145
00:07:01,934 --> 00:07:03,468
Hey, do you want
o.j. or milk
with your pancakes?

146
00:07:03,536 --> 00:07:05,637
Milk, please.
you got it.

147
00:07:05,705 --> 00:07:07,305
Hey, i think
we got spongebob

148
00:07:07,373 --> 00:07:09,241
Coming to visit us
for breakfast.

149
00:07:09,308 --> 00:07:10,809
Ahh, nice socks.

150
00:07:10,877 --> 00:07:12,844
Jim...

151
00:07:12,912 --> 00:07:14,412
I couldn't decide.

152
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:16,248
You know what,
i think it's great,

153
00:07:16,315 --> 00:07:18,350
And i am very impressed
with how you're getting
yourself ready.

154
00:07:18,417 --> 00:07:19,818
Thanks!

155
00:07:19,886 --> 00:07:21,520
You're welcome.

156
00:07:21,587 --> 00:07:24,122
So, is ned ok?

157
00:07:24,190 --> 00:07:25,790
Ned? why wouldn't he be?

158
00:07:25,858 --> 00:07:28,193
He called before.
didn't he?

159
00:07:30,696 --> 00:07:32,564
Well, someone called.

160
00:07:32,632 --> 00:07:34,766
I just didn't get
the chance to check it.

161
00:07:34,834 --> 00:07:37,335
I think ned
wants to talk to you.

162
00:07:39,705 --> 00:07:43,141
Yeah, i-i think
you could be
right about that.

163
00:07:43,209 --> 00:07:44,976
Um, your dad's going
to get the syrup.

164
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:49,881
[phone beeping]

165
00:07:51,384 --> 00:07:54,719
Woman: please
enter your password,
then press pound...

166
00:07:54,787 --> 00:07:57,155
Does this have
something to do
with your vision?

167
00:07:57,223 --> 00:07:58,823
Because as
the only member
of this family

168
00:07:58,891 --> 00:08:00,158
Who doesn't
traffic in ghosts,

169
00:08:00,226 --> 00:08:01,493
I'm kind of
at a loss.

170
00:08:01,561 --> 00:08:03,862
Well, all i know is,
i have a voicemail from ned.

171
00:08:03,930 --> 00:08:05,730
It came in this morning,
my phone was on vibrate.

172
00:08:05,798 --> 00:08:08,166
There is no way that aiden
would have known he called.

173
00:08:09,268 --> 00:08:10,702
But he did.

174
00:08:10,770 --> 00:08:12,337
What does this mean?

175
00:08:12,405 --> 00:08:15,707
That he's going
to continue to amaze us.

176
00:08:15,775 --> 00:08:17,342
And that whatever
has meaning to me

177
00:08:17,410 --> 00:08:19,544
Obviously means
something to him, too.

178
00:08:19,612 --> 00:08:22,981
Yeah, and ned means
a lot to both of you.

179
00:08:23,049 --> 00:08:24,316
Ned: hey, melinda.
it's ned.

180
00:08:24,383 --> 00:08:27,285
Something weird
happened at school.

181
00:08:27,353 --> 00:08:28,853
A friend of mine's
in trouble.

182
00:08:28,921 --> 00:08:31,189
What happened?

183
00:08:31,257 --> 00:08:32,691
Can you come over?

184
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:35,493
[exhales]

185
00:08:35,561 --> 00:08:38,063
[indistinct chatter]

186
00:08:39,599 --> 00:08:41,499
It was like this
when we came in,

187
00:08:41,567 --> 00:08:43,168
Only it was wet.

188
00:08:43,236 --> 00:08:44,202
It's nail polish.

189
00:08:44,270 --> 00:08:46,004
Melinda: yeah,
i can smell it.

190
00:08:46,072 --> 00:08:49,174
Look, i guess
someone could have
walked in here

191
00:08:49,242 --> 00:08:53,545
And hung my doll
and painted the walls

192
00:08:53,613 --> 00:08:56,214
In nail polish to make it
look like blood,

193
00:08:56,282 --> 00:09:00,418
But we were right here
when that mirror shattered.

194
00:09:00,486 --> 00:09:02,387
What caused that?

195
00:09:02,455 --> 00:09:04,422
Did you call
the campus cops?

196
00:09:04,490 --> 00:09:06,224
No, we called you.

197
00:09:06,292 --> 00:09:10,428
A friend of brianna's
died a few days ago...

198
00:09:10,496 --> 00:09:12,063
A friend
who was angry at her.

199
00:09:13,366 --> 00:09:15,767
Ned told me
what you can do.

200
00:09:15,835 --> 00:09:18,637
So...

201
00:09:18,704 --> 00:09:20,939
Is there one,

202
00:09:21,007 --> 00:09:23,408
Here?
no.

203
00:09:23,476 --> 00:09:26,244
No ghost.

204
00:09:26,312 --> 00:09:29,414
So, why don't you
tell me about
your friend who died.

205
00:09:32,018 --> 00:09:33,618
Gwen.

206
00:09:33,686 --> 00:09:36,955
We used
to be really tight.

207
00:09:37,023 --> 00:09:40,258
She was run down
by a car about a week ago.

208
00:09:53,939 --> 00:09:56,474
By then, we weren't
really speaking.

209
00:09:56,542 --> 00:09:57,509
What happened?

210
00:09:57,576 --> 00:09:59,144
I saw her at a party.

211
00:09:59,211 --> 00:10:01,279
She was making out
with a guy.

212
00:10:01,347 --> 00:10:03,415
She had a boyfriend

213
00:10:03,482 --> 00:10:06,951
Who was a good friend
of mine, too.

214
00:10:07,019 --> 00:10:10,922
It ticked me off,
so i told a friend

215
00:10:10,990 --> 00:10:12,023
Who told a friend--

216
00:10:12,091 --> 00:10:13,625
Who told her boyfriend.

217
00:10:13,693 --> 00:10:15,327
Gwen was really upset.

218
00:10:15,394 --> 00:10:17,529
Upset enough
to do all this?

219
00:10:17,596 --> 00:10:21,199
Actually, there's
one more thing.

220
00:10:21,267 --> 00:10:24,502
Can a ghost send an email?

221
00:10:25,938 --> 00:10:27,872
"hello, my name
is sally stitch.

222
00:10:27,940 --> 00:10:29,774
"i have chosen you.
forward this,

223
00:10:29,842 --> 00:10:31,943
"or you or someone
you love will suffer.

224
00:10:32,011 --> 00:10:34,546
Do not break the chain,
or the suffering
will have no end."

225
00:10:34,613 --> 00:10:36,514
Wow. that's
pretty disturbing.

226
00:10:36,582 --> 00:10:38,183
This gwen's email?

227
00:10:38,250 --> 00:10:39,851
Yep.

228
00:10:39,919 --> 00:10:41,353
I got it a few days ago.

229
00:10:41,420 --> 00:10:43,054
I didn't forward it.

230
00:10:43,122 --> 00:10:44,956
Guess that made her mad.

231
00:10:45,024 --> 00:10:46,725
And it came
after gwen died?

232
00:10:46,792 --> 00:10:49,060
Two days after,
according to the timestamp.

233
00:10:49,128 --> 00:10:51,496
So the image of
this girl with her
eyes stitched shut,

234
00:10:51,564 --> 00:10:53,498
Would that
mean anything
to you and gwen?

235
00:10:53,566 --> 00:10:55,233
No.
so it could be

236
00:10:55,301 --> 00:10:57,168
Some chain email
gwen got
and forwarded.

237
00:10:57,236 --> 00:10:59,671
Except that's not
all she did.

238
00:10:59,739 --> 00:11:02,374
She's the only one
who could have known.

239
00:11:02,441 --> 00:11:04,576
Known what?
look at this.

240
00:11:04,643 --> 00:11:06,878
At the end of the email,
there are these descriptions

241
00:11:06,946 --> 00:11:09,547
Of what happened to people
who broke the chain.

242
00:11:11,217 --> 00:11:12,917
"a college student
ignored the email

243
00:11:12,985 --> 00:11:14,486
"and found
her best friend luanne

244
00:11:14,553 --> 00:11:17,555
Hanging from a noose in
a blood-splattered closet."

245
00:11:17,623 --> 00:11:19,324
Like your doll.

246
00:11:19,392 --> 00:11:22,227
Luanne is my doll.

247
00:11:22,294 --> 00:11:25,196
She's a keepsake i've had
since i was six.

248
00:11:25,264 --> 00:11:28,133
Gwen is the only one
who knew she what
she meant to me.

249
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:30,635
She's the only one
who even knew her name.

250
00:11:33,072 --> 00:11:35,173
[birds chirping]

251
00:11:35,241 --> 00:11:37,675
Eli: ghosts are creating
their own emails now?

252
00:11:37,743 --> 00:11:39,177
Aren't they
getting crafty.

253
00:11:39,245 --> 00:11:41,079
What's next,
blogging? webisodes?

254
00:11:41,147 --> 00:11:43,515
Well, it's possible gwen
didn't create the email.

255
00:11:43,582 --> 00:11:44,450
It's just something
going around--

256
00:11:44,518 --> 00:11:46,786
A scary image
she's using to
terrorize her friends.

257
00:11:46,853 --> 00:11:48,320
