We have to prove
that she and that email
are not real.

515
00:24:30,142 --> 00:24:32,710
Any chance
you could figure out
who created it?

516
00:24:32,778 --> 00:24:33,978
[scoffs]
fat chance.

517
00:24:34,046 --> 00:24:35,746
Yeah.
i mean, that thing

518
00:24:35,814 --> 00:24:38,082
Could have been
going around for months
before gwen even got it.

519
00:24:38,150 --> 00:24:39,917
Yeah, the email's building.
i mean, every time
somebody gets hurt,

520
00:24:39,985 --> 00:24:41,519
It just makes gwen's case.

521
00:24:41,586 --> 00:24:43,054
What are you
going to do,

522
00:24:43,121 --> 00:24:45,022
Travel the speed of
d.s.l. to prove each
one was an accident?

523
00:24:45,090 --> 00:24:48,826
No. just the one
who turned her into
a believer and a ghost.

524
00:24:48,894 --> 00:24:51,162
Wait, gwen's obit
says she died
in a car accident.

525
00:24:51,229 --> 00:24:54,031
But we know that she was
disoriented from
the other accident,

526
00:24:54,099 --> 00:24:55,866
Two car accident.

527
00:24:55,934 --> 00:24:57,668
There was a witness.

528
00:24:57,736 --> 00:24:58,769
The other driver.

529
00:24:58,837 --> 00:25:01,105
Can you get your hands
on a police report?

530
00:25:06,144 --> 00:25:08,579
Thank you.

531
00:25:08,647 --> 00:25:10,815
I really appreciate you
taking the time to talk.

532
00:25:10,882 --> 00:25:12,516
Well, i was due
a break, anyways.

533
00:25:12,584 --> 00:25:13,851
So you're a therapist?

534
00:25:13,919 --> 00:25:15,720
And a grief counselor.
up at the university.

535
00:25:15,787 --> 00:25:17,655
Right. you mentioned that
on the phone.

536
00:25:17,723 --> 00:25:20,791
The girl, the one that died,
she was a student there.

537
00:25:20,859 --> 00:25:22,760
Yeah. i'm trying to help
some of her friends

538
00:25:22,828 --> 00:25:24,261
Make sense
of the tragedy.

539
00:25:24,329 --> 00:25:25,930
Make sense
of a freak accident.

540
00:25:25,998 --> 00:25:27,698
How are you supposed
to do that?

541
00:25:27,766 --> 00:25:29,000
Well, sometimes
it can be comforting

542
00:25:29,067 --> 00:25:30,267
If people think
there's a reason

543
00:25:30,335 --> 00:25:31,769
Why something
like this happened.

544
00:25:31,837 --> 00:25:33,237
A woman runs a red light.

545
00:25:33,305 --> 00:25:35,072
Where's the reason in that?
good question.

546
00:25:35,140 --> 00:25:36,707
So, from
your point of view,

547
00:25:36,775 --> 00:25:38,776
There's no way
to explain
what happened.

548
00:25:38,844 --> 00:25:41,312
I didn't say that.
tell me.

549
00:25:41,380 --> 00:25:44,448
Well, there was a moment
just before the crash.

550
00:25:44,516 --> 00:25:47,284
I was making a left,
so i pulled out.

551
00:25:47,352 --> 00:25:49,520
Then i saw her coming.

552
00:25:49,588 --> 00:25:52,456
But there was still
plenty of time
for her to stop.

553
00:25:52,524 --> 00:25:55,393
Normally when
someone runs a red,

554
00:25:55,460 --> 00:25:58,662
You think cell phone
or make-up, a radio.

555
00:25:58,730 --> 00:26:00,498
You know, there's
some distraction.

556
00:26:00,565 --> 00:26:03,868
But she was staring
straight ahead.

557
00:26:05,971 --> 00:26:09,607
Her eyes glazed over
like--like she was frozen.

558
00:26:09,674 --> 00:26:11,175
Didn't even blink.

559
00:26:13,612 --> 00:26:14,812
Whoa!

560
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:17,415
It was like
she was in a trance.

561
00:26:19,751 --> 00:26:23,287
In a trance.
that's what he said?

562
00:26:23,355 --> 00:26:26,090
She looked right at him,
but she didn't seem to see him.

563
00:26:26,158 --> 00:26:27,491
What would
make her do that?

564
00:26:27,559 --> 00:26:29,527
Plenty of things.
she could have been having

565
00:26:29,594 --> 00:26:31,295
What my father called
an "episode."

566
00:26:31,363 --> 00:26:32,963
She could have
gotten her meds wrong.

567
00:26:33,031 --> 00:26:34,632
Could have had too much wine
after dinner.

568
00:26:34,699 --> 00:26:36,133
Any one of which
can be confirmed

569
00:26:36,201 --> 00:26:37,701
With a little bit
of follow-up.

570
00:26:37,769 --> 00:26:39,136
Yeah.

571
00:26:39,204 --> 00:26:40,638
And prove to the ghost
that it wasn't a curse,

572
00:26:40,705 --> 00:26:43,307
And i can stop reading
my emails through
closed fingers.

573
00:26:44,342 --> 00:26:45,543
What if we can't
confirm it?

574
00:26:45,610 --> 00:26:47,344
What if we can't
find a reasonable
explanation?

575
00:26:47,412 --> 00:26:49,146
I got back
to mail with stamps.

576
00:26:49,214 --> 00:26:51,148
Shouldn't we be looking
for other explanations?

577
00:26:51,216 --> 00:26:53,417
Like what?
like, there's a curse.

578
00:26:53,485 --> 00:26:55,252
See, this is why
i think economics

579
00:26:55,320 --> 00:26:57,088
Would have been
a better choice
of major for you

580
00:26:57,155 --> 00:26:59,123
Than anthropology
of the occult.

581
00:26:59,191 --> 00:27:01,358
Come on, you're gonna
tell me you've never
thought about it?

582
00:27:01,426 --> 00:27:03,561
<i>you've read
the book of changes.</i>

583
00:27:03,628 --> 00:27:04,929
Yeah, but only
in the bright sunlight

584
00:27:04,996 --> 00:27:06,564
With garlic and a cross
wrapped around my neck.

585
00:27:06,631 --> 00:27:08,065
Because you know
there's more
out there

586
00:27:08,133 --> 00:27:09,467
Than what you can
see with your eyes.

587
00:27:09,534 --> 00:27:11,068
When i can hear it
with my ears, sure.

588
00:27:11,136 --> 00:27:13,337
But, ned, come on,
you're not going
to convince me

589
00:27:13,405 --> 00:27:15,506
That this email's
carrying some kind of spell.

590
00:27:15,574 --> 00:27:17,641
'cause you don't
believe in anything
you can't see or hear.

591
00:27:17,709 --> 00:27:19,677
I try not to.
yeah.

592
00:27:19,744 --> 00:27:23,047
It's not really
an option for me.

593
00:27:23,115 --> 00:27:25,483
I know ghosts
are real even though
i can't see them.

594
00:27:25,550 --> 00:27:27,318
What's hard
for me to believe

595
00:27:27,385 --> 00:27:30,387
Is that ghosts are
the only things out
there that i can't see.

596
00:27:37,629 --> 00:27:40,231
[thunder]

597
00:27:40,298 --> 00:27:42,266
[door creaks]

598
00:27:42,334 --> 00:27:43,834
[floorboards creaking]

599
00:27:43,902 --> 00:27:45,903
[telephone rings]

600
00:27:47,272 --> 00:27:48,506
[ring]

601
00:27:48,573 --> 00:27:50,941
[sighs]

602
00:27:51,009 --> 00:27:53,711
[ring]

603
00:27:53,778 --> 00:27:55,513
[gasping]

604
00:27:55,580 --> 00:27:57,081
[ring]

605
00:27:57,149 --> 00:27:59,550
Melinda, on answering machine:
hey, it's melinda.
talk at the beep.

606
00:27:59,618 --> 00:28:00,918
[loud beep]

607
00:28:00,986 --> 00:28:02,853
Jim: hey. hey,
how are you doing there?

608
00:28:02,921 --> 00:28:04,488
I'm just checking in.

609
00:28:04,556 --> 00:28:06,357
Looks like i'm going
to be stuck here

610
00:28:06,424 --> 00:28:07,491
For another couple of hours.

611
00:28:07,559 --> 00:28:10,227
I wanted to tell you
something. it, uh,

612
00:28:10,295 --> 00:28:13,731
Looks like that email chain
finally reached the hospital.

613
00:28:13,798 --> 00:28:16,133
Two e.r. nurses,
dave in admitting,

614
00:28:16,201 --> 00:28:18,736
And, well, actually me.

615
00:28:18,803 --> 00:28:21,238
I'm thinking
you're probably
still with aiden.

616
00:28:21,306 --> 00:28:23,007
Call me now, huh?

617
00:28:23,074 --> 00:28:24,775
I won't do anything
till i hear from you.

618
00:28:24,843 --> 00:28:26,644
All right? bye.

619
00:28:30,015 --> 00:28:31,415
[thunder]

620
00:28:37,455 --> 00:28:40,257
[screaming]

621
00:28:40,325 --> 00:28:42,660
Aiden: mommy?

622
00:28:46,631 --> 00:28:48,399
Aiden?

623
00:28:48,466 --> 00:28:50,134
Are you ok?

624
00:28:50,202 --> 00:28:51,969
Did you have
a bad dream?

625
00:28:52,037 --> 00:28:54,939
I don't know.
i don't remember.

626
00:28:55,006 --> 00:28:56,340
Did you?

627
00:28:56,408 --> 00:28:57,775
Kinda.

628
00:28:57,842 --> 00:28:59,476
Do you need a hug?

629
00:28:59,544 --> 00:29:01,212
Yeah.

630
00:29:04,249 --> 00:29:06,417
[gasping]

631
00:29:06,484 --> 00:29:08,285
Oh.

632
00:29:16,004 --> 00:29:18,639
[horn honking]
melinda: hey, aiden!

633
00:29:18,707 --> 00:29:20,508
Your lunch.

634
00:29:20,576 --> 00:29:22,243
Thanks!

635
00:29:22,311 --> 00:29:24,011
Don't come
with me, mom.

636
00:29:24,079 --> 00:29:25,980
I'm not. i'm just
gonna watch.

637
00:29:26,048 --> 00:29:27,048
Love you guys.

638
00:29:27,115 --> 00:29:29,450
Love you, too.
love you.

639
00:29:29,518 --> 00:29:30,551
[chuckles]

640
00:29:30,619 --> 00:29:32,220
God, he's so brave.

641
00:29:32,287 --> 00:29:33,888
[laughter]

642
00:29:33,956 --> 00:29:36,691
Hmm. it's because
he doesn't know
what you know.

643
00:29:36,758 --> 00:29:38,559
And he doesn't remember
his dreams.

644
00:29:38,627 --> 00:29:40,328
Hey, i'm so sorry
i wasn't here last night.

645
00:29:40,395 --> 00:29:41,662
That sounded
like a bad one.

646
00:29:41,730 --> 00:29:43,264
Yeah, it felt so real.

647
00:29:43,332 --> 00:29:44,932
Yeah.

648
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:46,867
It feels pretty real
to gwen, too.

649
00:29:46,935 --> 00:29:49,070
She gets a creepy,
threatening email,

650
00:29:49,137 --> 00:29:50,738
She ignores
the warning
to forward it,

651
00:29:50,806 --> 00:29:52,573
And wham,
car accident,
she's dead.

652
00:29:52,641 --> 00:29:54,242
Her mother's hanging
by a thread.

653
00:29:54,309 --> 00:29:56,577
Yeah, i'm starting
to wonder about
the power of that email.

654
00:29:56,645 --> 00:29:58,312
How's an email
have power?

655
00:29:58,380 --> 00:29:59,981
Well, if there's
a ghost attached to it.

656
00:30:00,048 --> 00:30:01,649
The one who started
this whole thing,

657
00:30:01,717 --> 00:30:04,652
The one's who's feeding off
the fear it spreads.

658
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:06,320
Wait, you're talking
about another ghost.

659
00:30:06,388 --> 00:30:07,355
Sally stitch?

660
00:30:07,422 --> 00:30:08,823
It would explain
my visions.

661
00:30:08,890 --> 00:30:11,359
You know, i mean,
ned said that
hundreds of years ago,

662
00:30:11,426 --> 00:30:13,928
There was this practice,
this punishment--

663
00:30:13,996 --> 00:30:16,264
Wait, wait, you don't
believe that there
really was a girl

664
00:30:16,331 --> 00:30:18,566
Who had her eyes
and mouth stitched shut

665
00:30:18,634 --> 00:30:21,002
And now she's creating
chain emails

666
00:30:21,069 --> 00:30:22,236
To do what?
spread the misery.

667
00:30:22,304 --> 00:30:23,904
I mean, if you can
reach thousands

668
00:30:23,972 --> 00:30:25,773
And millions of people
on the internet...

669
00:30:25,841 --> 00:30:27,575
You can spread
some misery.

670
00:30:27,643 --> 00:30:30,778
Wow. but now
the visions are
coming through aiden?

671
00:30:30,846 --> 00:30:32,913
I think he was
channeling them to me.

672
00:30:32,981 --> 00:30:34,815
I mean, they stopped
every time that he woke up.

673
00:30:34,883 --> 00:30:37,652
Although, they originally
came from her.

674
00:30:37,719 --> 00:30:41,188
All right.
so, you think
sally stitch

675
00:30:41,256 --> 00:30:44,392
Caused the accident
that killed gwen
and hurt her mom?

676
00:30:44,459 --> 00:30:47,061
The driver said
that she was staring at him,

677
00:30:47,129 --> 00:30:49,063
Like she was in
some kind of trance.

678
00:30:49,131 --> 00:30:51,232
Or if she was
blinded,

679
00:30:51,300 --> 00:30:53,000
Like you were
in your vision.

680
00:30:53,068 --> 00:30:55,369
Ok, see the wheels turning,
but what?

681
00:30:55,437 --> 00:30:56,804
You see, this accident,
it always bothered me,

682
00:30:56,872 --> 00:30:58,139
'cause it was
low impact.

683
00:30:58,206 --> 00:31:00,141
But then how does gwen's
mother end up in a coma?

684
00:31:00,208 --> 00:31:02,143
The doctors thought
the same thing, too,

685
00:31:02,210 --> 00:31:04,011
And they sent her
to an m.r.i.

686
00:31:04,079 --> 00:31:06,514
Yeah, so what
were they looking for?

687
00:31:06,581 --> 00:31:08,949
To see if she'd
had a stroke.

688
00:31:09,017 --> 00:31:10,718
I mean,
think about it.
it makes sense.

689
00:31:10,786 --> 00:31:12,286
You said in your
vision you weren't
totally blinded,

690
00:31:12,354 --> 00:31:13,454
You saw little
slivers of light?

691
00:31:13,522 --> 00:31:14,622
What i saw
through the stitches.

692
00:31:14,690 --> 00:31:16,157
That's what happens
to stroke victims.

693
00:31:16,224 --> 00:31:18,292
Before it goes black,
they see these little
pin pricks of light.

694
00:31:18,360 --> 00:31:19,460
You're brilliant!

695
00:31:19,528 --> 00:31:20,795
No. i think
i'm probably wrong.

696
00:31:20,862 --> 00:31:22,196
Yeah, but you're still
totally brilliant.

697
00:31:22,264 --> 00:31:23,764
I'm gonna be late.
look, i'll call you

698
00:31:23,832 --> 00:31:25,266
If i learn anything
from the hospital.

699
00:31:25,334 --> 00:31:26,534
Great.
[cell phone rings]

700
00:31:26,601 --> 00:31:27,635
Hey. what's up?

701
00:31:27,703 --> 00:31:29,670
Ok, so we couldn't
convince the ghost

702
00:31:29,738 --> 00:31:31,806
That an accident
was just that--
an accident.

703
00:31:31,873 --> 00:31:33,574
Well, jim is close.

704
00:31:33,642 --> 00:31:35,876
I'm proving
the email's a hoax
by locating its author.

705
00:31:35,944 --> 00:31:38,713
Impossible,
right? a needle in
a gazillion haystacks?

706
00:31:38,780 --> 00:31:40,614
Ah, i am sensing
triumph here.

707
00:31:40,682 --> 00:31:42,616
I found it.
hey, i helped!

708
00:31:42,684 --> 00:31:45,386
The creator of the email,
the evil mythical sally stitch,

709
00:31:45,454 --> 00:31:46,754
We got a name.

710
00:31:46,822 --> 00:31:48,723
J. miller.
hey!

711
00:31:48,790 --> 00:31:50,257
Ok, well, is this
j. miller alive?

712
00:31:50,325 --> 00:31:52,293
Not just alive, living.
and you'll never guess where.

713
00:31:52,361 --> 00:31:55,496
Right here in grandview.

714
00:31:55,564 --> 00:31:57,998
[siren]

715
00:31:58,066 --> 00:31:59,533
Woman on p.a.:
dr. morris, dial--

716
00:31:59,601 --> 00:32:01,202
Don't be
gender-biased here.

717
00:32:01,269 --> 00:32:03,037
Male, female, j. miller
could be anyone.

718
00:32:03,105 --> 00:32:04,772
Yeah, except
thankfully a ghost.

719
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:05,973
Did you ever think
it might be?

720
00:32:06,041 --> 00:32:07,141
For a minute.

721
00:32:07,209 --> 00:32:08,542
A brief, dark minute.

722
00:32:08,610 --> 00:32:10,344
So we get double
brownie points

723
00:32:10,412 --> 00:32:12,513
Finding a living,
non-ghost person
wrote this email?

724
00:32:12,581 --> 00:32:14,482
Um, triple if this person
convinces gwen

725
00:32:14,549 --> 00:32:16,417
There's no spell.
[beep]

726
00:32:16,485 --> 00:32:18,786
Well, it may be
a moot point.

727
00:32:18,854 --> 00:32:20,654
I can't access
the employee files.

728
00:32:20,722 --> 00:32:22,990
Well, try harder.
this person works
here, or did.

729
00:32:23,058 --> 00:32:24,792
They've got a hospital
email address.

730
00:32:24,860 --> 00:32:26,961
Which would explain
how they knew gwen.

731
00:32:27,028 --> 00:32:30,231
Brianna said they both
volunteered here
over spring break.

732
00:32:30,298 --> 00:32:34,402
Uh, except the person
didn't actually work here.

733
00:32:34,469 --> 00:32:37,304
Her name's julia miller,
and she was a patient.

734
00:32:37,372 --> 00:32:38,806
Still is.

735
00:32:38,874 --> 00:32:40,708
According to this,
she has a.m.l.,

736
00:32:40,776 --> 00:32:42,877
An acute type
of leukemia.

737
00:32:42,944 --> 00:32:45,846
Patient? why would
she have a hospital
email address?

738
00:32:45,914 --> 00:32:47,515
Because she's lived here.

739
00:32:47,582 --> 00:32:50,551
Her whole life.

740
00:32:55,724 --> 00:32:58,993
Melinda:
she's just a child.

741
00:32:59,060 --> 00:33:00,628
She really lives here.

742
00:33:00,695 --> 00:33:02,329
Apparently,
the treatments

743
00:33:02,397 --> 00:33:04,231
Make julia
vulnerable
to infection.

744
00:33:04,299 --> 00:33:06,634
That's why
she couldn't leave.

745
00:33:06,701 --> 00:33:08,169
Can you imagine
growing up here?

746
00:33:08,236 --> 00:33:09,870
No, i can't.

747
00:33:09,938 --> 00:33:12,239
Maybe that's why
she made up sally stitch--

748
00:33:12,307 --> 00:33:13,707
A coping device.

749
00:33:13,775 --> 00:33:16,010
A way for her to deal
with the creepiness
of this place.

750
00:33:16,077 --> 00:33:17,344
She put a face to it.

751
00:33:17,412 --> 00:33:20,014
Do you think she has
any idea what she started?

752
00:33:23,952 --> 00:33:25,619
I'm going to go
look for her doctor,

753
00:33:25,687 --> 00:33:27,455
See what else
i can find out.

754
00:33:29,324 --> 00:33:31,692
I told you this would happen,
but you wouldn't listen.

755
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:33,327
What happened?
what's wrong?

756
00:33:33,395 --> 00:33:35,162
You wouldn't do
what she wanted,

757
00:33:35,230 --> 00:33:36,665
And now she's dying!
who's dying?

758
00:33:36,666 --> 00:33:37,666
My mom.

759
00:33:37,732 --> 00:33:40,100
Woman on p.a.:
trauma team to i.c.u.
on six west.

760
00:33:40,168 --> 00:33:41,569
Oh, my god.

761
00:33:48,577 --> 00:33:50,444
[monitor beeping]

